{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"alias":"wormy-sod-gorge","description":"## What\nCut the **v0.7.0** minor release of `nava-rebar` following `docs/releasing.md`, and\nin doing so **dogfood** the newly-merged `github_release` job (ticket\nf112-6222-e236-4b09, change 314): pushing the `v0.7.0` tag must now *automatically*\ncreate the GitHub Release — no manual `gh release create`. 198 commits have landed\nsince v0.6.0 (grounding pyright backend, typed public return contracts, MCP tool\nannotations, supply-chain hardening, plus many fixes/docs), so a minor bump is warranted.\n\n## Scope / steps (per docs/releasing.md)\n- Bump `pyproject.toml` `version` and `server.json` (`version` + `packages[0].version`) to 0.7.0.\n- Land the \"Release 0.7.0\" bump commit on `main` through Gerrit (both votes).\n- Tag `v0.7.0` and push the tag → `release.yml` publishes to PyPI (OIDC) and the new\n  `github_release` job auto-creates the GitHub Release.\n- Update the Homebrew tap (`navapbc/homebrew-rebar` `Formula/rebar.rb`: url + sha256).\n- Update the MCP Registry (`mcp-publisher publish` of `server.json`).\n- Post-release smoke test (`scripts/probe-rebar.sh` against the published artifact).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `pyproject.toml` and `server.json` both read version 0.7.0 and the bump is merged to main via Gerrit.\n- [ ] PyPI shows nava-rebar 0.7.0 live.\n- [ ] The GitHub Release for v0.7.0 was created **automatically** by the workflow (not by hand) and is marked Latest.\n- [ ] Homebrew formula points at the 0.7.0 sdist (correct url + sha256).\n- [ ] MCP Registry serves io.github.navapbc/rebar at 0.7.0.\n- [ ] Post-release probe passes against the published artifact.","id":"7e0c-e76a-75c5-420d","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Release nava-rebar 0.7.0 across all channels (dogfood auto GitHub Release)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783302151149679001,"uuid":"a3c00265-61d2-4a85-aa02-aec069acc9e7"}